# Blog Writing Style

## Tone

- First person narrative: "I learned...", "I discovered...", "When I first saw..."
- Conversational but technically accurate
- Learning-first: explain "why" before "how"
- Honest about mistakes: "Here's what I got wrong..."

## Code Examples

- Practical, runnable code with language tags (`tsx`, `typescript`, `javascript`)
- Show "wrong" approach first, then "right" approach with explanation
- Comments on key parts only — no narration comments

## Formatting

- `**Bold**` for key terms on first introduction only
- `Backticks` for inline code, file names, technical terms
- `---` horizontal rules between major sections
- Emoji only in closing: "Happy coding!"

## Gotchas

- **Title field**: Always use double quotes (`title: "Don't Do This"`) — single quotes break on apostrophes
- **Excerpt**: Use `>-` for multi-line values
- **Slug consistency**: Must match between frontmatter `slug`, filename, and quiz `quizId`

## Publishing Workflow

1. Create as draft in `content/blog/drafts/{slug}.mdx` with `draft: true`
2. Create quiz at `content/blog/quizzes/{slug}-quiz.json`
3. To publish: move to `content/blog/{slug}.mdx`, set `draft: false`, set `publishedAt` to today
